To solve for the opposite of $(-\sqrt{3})^{2}$, we follow these steps:

1. Calculate $(-\sqrt{3})^{2}$:
   \begin{align*}
   (-\sqrt{3})^{2} &= (-\sqrt{3}) \times (-\sqrt{3}) \\
   &= \sqrt{3} \times \sqrt{3} \\
   &= 3
   \end{align*}

2. Find the opposite of the result:
   \begin{align*}
   \text{Opposite of } 3 &= -3
   \end{align*}

Therefore, the opposite of $(-\sqrt{3})^{2}$ is $\boxed{-3}$.

