$$\begin{array}{l}
x^{2}+y^{2}+z^{2}=\frac{x^{2}}{1}+\frac{y^{2}}{1}+\frac{z^{2}}{1} \\
\geqslant \frac{(x+y+z)^{2}}{1+1+1}=\frac{1}{3}
\end{array}$$

i.e., $x^{2}+y^{2}+z^{2} \geqslant \frac{1}{3}$.
$$\begin{array}{l}
\text { Therefore, } \frac{x}{\lambda-\mu x}+\frac{y}{\lambda-\mu y}+\frac{z}{\lambda-\mu z} \\
=\frac{x^{2}}{\lambda x-\mu x^{2}}+\frac{y^{2}}{\lambda y-\mu y^{2}}+\frac{z^{2}}{\lambda z-\mu z^{2}} \\
\geqslant \frac{(x+y+z)^{2}}{\lambda(x+y+z)-\mu\left(x^{2}+y^{2}+z^{2}\right)} \\
\geqslant \frac{1}{\lambda-\frac{1}{3} \mu}=\frac{3}{3 \lambda-\mu}
\end{array}$$

